---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
export const prerender = true;
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---
<Base title="Home" active="home">

  <section class="hero">
    <img
      class="hero-logo"
      src={`${base}favicon.png`}
      alt="Birds, Bugs & Botanicals logo"
      width="96"
      height="96"
    />
    <h1>Birds, Bugs &amp; Botanicals</h1>
    <p class="tagline">
      One organism a day — a photo, a fact, and a soundscape to go with it.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What this is</h2>
    <p>
      Birds, Bugs &amp; Botanicals is a nature-education social media page. Each day
      we feature a single bird, insect, or plant with a real photo, a short set of
      facts, and sometimes a brief AI-generated video — all paired with a soothing
      natural soundscape. The goal is simple: teach people something true and
      interesting about the natural world, and make them a little more excited to
      go spend time in it.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>How content gets posted</h2>
    <p>
      This site exists to document a small internal tool that supports the page:
      an automated Python script that we run ourselves to publish content to our
      TikTok account through TikTok's official API. Each day, the script:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>selects the day's featured bird, bug, or plant,</li>
      <li>puts together the accompanying photo or video and a short factual caption, and</li>
      <li>publishes that post directly to the Birds, Bugs &amp; Botanicals TikTok account.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      The tool has no public interface and no user accounts. It doesn't accept
      input from other people, and it doesn't read, collect, or interact with
      data belonging to other TikTok users — it only ever posts our own original
      content to our own account, on our own schedule.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Legal</h2>
    <p>
      Details on how we handle information and the terms under which the app
      operates are here:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href={`${base}terms-of-service/`}>Terms of Service</a></li>
      <li><a href={`${base}privacy-policy/`}>Privacy Policy</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about the page or the app can be sent to 
      <a href="mailto:birdsbugsbotanicals@proton.me">birdsbugsbotanicals@proton.me</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

</Base>

<style>
  .hero {
    text-align: center;
    padding-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .hero-logo {
    border-radius: 22px;
    object-fit: cover;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }

  .hero h1 {
    margin: 0 0 6px;
  }

  .tagline {
    color: #6b7568;
    font-size: 1.05em;
    margin-top: 0 !important;
  }

  ul {
    padding-left: 1.3em;
  }

  li {
    margin: 0.4em 0;
  }
</style>
